educate yourself on the table dlls in fitness_db

The table definitions (DDL) for all tables in the fitness_db database, including Products, SaleDetails, ServiceTickets, Sales, and Customers, have been retrieved.

Key Observations

  • The Products table stores information about the fitness products, including product ID, name, type, brand, price, and stock quantity.
  • The SaleDetails table captures individual items within a sale, referencing both Sales and Products tables to link sales transactions with the specific products sold, including quantity and unit price.
  • The ServiceTickets table tracks customer service requests, including ticket details, customer and product associations, issue description, status, and resolution date.
  • The Sales table records sales transactions, linking customers to sales with timestamp and total amount, including a sales person ID.
  • The Customers table holds customer information such as name, contact details, address, and registration date.

SQL DDL: fitness_db.Products 
CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.Products ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductName VARCHAR(100) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC NOT NULL,
      ProductType VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Brand VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
      StockQuantity INTEGER)
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( ProductID );
SQL DDL: fitness_db.SaleDetails 
CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.SaleDetails ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      SaleDetailID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      SaleID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      Quantity INTEGER NOT NULL,
      UnitPrice DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL, 
FOREIGN KEY ( SaleID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Sales ( SaleID ),
FOREIGN KEY ( ProductID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Products ( ProductID ))
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( SaleDetailID );

     (

      IssueDescription VARCHAR(1000) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,

FOREIGN KEY ( CustomerID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Customers ( CustomerID ),
FOREIGN KEY ( ProductID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Products ( ProductID ))
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( TicketID );

     (
      SaleID INTEGER NOT NULL,
